**Version Used**: VS 18.0.0 Insiders

**Steps to Reproduce**:
At the marked location, open the lightbulb menu and select "Convert to switch statement".
```csharp
record R(int? P);

class C
{
    int M(R v)
    {
        $$if (v.P == 0)
        {
            return 1;
        }

        if (v.P is { } b && b > 0)
        {
            return 2;
        }

        return 0;
    }
}
```

**Expected Behavior**:
```csharp
int M(R v)
{
    switch (v.P)
    {
        case 0:
            return 1;
        case { } b when b > 0:
            return 2;
        default:
            return 0;
    }
}
```

**Actual Behavior**:
An extra linebreak is added before the pattern matching:
```csharp
int M(R v)
{
    switch (v.P)
    {
        case 0:
            return 1;
        case // <- Additional line break
        { } b when b > 0:
            return 2;
        default:
            return 0;
    }
}
```

